-- Allied Irish Plans $7.3 Billion Underwritten Capital Raising in November
-- B y   L o u i s a   F a h y
-- 2010-09-30T06:07:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-30/allied-irish-plans-5-4-billion-euro-capital-raising-in-november.html
Allied Irish Banks Plc will launch
a 5.4 billion-euro capital raising in November, it said today in
a statement.  The capital raising will be fully underwritten by the
National Pensions Reserve Fund Commission at a fixed price of
0.50 euro per new ordinary share, a discount of about 9.4
percent to the closing price on Sept. 29.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Louisa Fahy at 
 lnesbitt@bloomberg.net  